    &lt;Title&gt;Smashed Ankle :(&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Chris Place&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I smashed my ankle pretty badly whilst mountain biking up in the Peak District this June. Turns out I did a pretty good job of it, Mountain Rescue job, the works.

I just wanted to get in touch to say what an amazing level of service, professionalism and com-fort I received whilst under your Orthopaedic team, and all the wonderful staff on Ward D1 this June. I can’t remember all the names of the anaesthetists, doctors and nurses but every single one of them was a credit to your hospital, and when I can walk again I will be sure to pop by and say thanks in person. Thanks for helping me deal with the initial trauma both physically and mentally. The care I received was amazing and sincere, and in such testing times for our NHS I experienced no ill feeling or angst against it. Care and compassion was the only infection spreading on Ward D1.

I was admitted to A&amp;amp;amp;E with quite a serious fracture (Grade 1 open tibial pilon fracture) to my ankle. This fracture was reduced and fixed in position by an absolute hero that I can’t name on here. I don’t think at the time I fully appreciated the seriousness of the situation as the mor-phine was flowing, I think the initial job was to rescue my foot! Thankfully that was achieved. 

What an amazing job all your staff did, from the nurses comforting me and my wife in A&amp;amp;amp;E to the healthcare assistants and the wonderful tea trolley. The whole experience of Stepping Hill was fantastic and I can’t praise everyone enough.

So I still have a foot and am on with the long journey of rehabilitation. After my stay at your hospital I then went to Liverpool Royal and received a wonderful addition to my leg ‘Ilizarov Apparatus’, which is pretty brutal, but its doing a good job. It is just the start of my journey, but what a start I had.

THANK YOU SO MUCH&lt;/CommentText&gt;
